                "position": 630
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.01436/2607.01436v1/figures/fig_infill_src.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Completing a gap from both sides.One sentence of a chest X-ray report is masked\n(the gap) and filled from the surrounding fixed fragments. Top: the diffusion model draws on\nfragments on either side and recovers the sentence correctly. Bottom: the autoregressive sibling\nsees only the fragments before it, the rest greyed out, and reconstructs it incorrectly. RealMIMIC-CXRexample.",
